WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.031 --> 00:00:01.531
www.beast.run

00:00:03.382 --> 00:00:05.812
[Music]

00:00:08.121 --> 00:00:11.770
Imagine having just one lightweight backpack that's good for anything,

00:00:12.217 --> 00:00:16.413
from short day hikes to long mountain trips or even family outings.

00:00:18.233 --> 00:00:21.491
This is the Tornado Vest Pack by Hanchor and Beast Runners.

00:00:22.269 --> 00:00:25.874
Let's see if it's the all-in-one solution for every adventure.

00:00:30.818 --> 00:00:32.764
Hi, I'm Petr from Beast Runners 跑山獸.

00:00:32.950 --> 00:00:35.777
Today I am reviewing the TORNADO Vest Pack

00:00:35.967 --> 00:00:38.445
after testing it in Taiwan's mountains.

00:00:39.100 --> 00:00:42.831
We team up with Hanchor, a popular backpack maker from Taiwan,

00:00:43.054 --> 00:00:44.873
to create Tornado Vest Pack.

00:00:45.884 --> 00:00:47.089
We made these partnership

00:00:47.201 --> 00:00:50.381
because mountain activities have become really popular in Taiwan.

00:00:51.307 --> 00:00:54.221
As trail runners, we often have problems with backpacks

00:00:54.410 --> 00:00:58.640
that were too small or lack safety features for longer trips.

00:00:58.986 --> 00:01:03.341
The Tornado Vest Pack solves this by offering a 32-Liter capacity

00:01:03.567 --> 00:01:06.778
while still being comfortable and easy to move with.

00:01:08.809 --> 00:01:12.865
The Tornado Vest Pack is made for both hikers and trail runners.

00:01:13.943 --> 00:01:17.303
It gives you more safety and enough space for your gear

00:01:17.396 --> 00:01:20.600
 on long difficult trips in the mountains.

00:01:24.232 --> 00:01:27.958
This pack is for people who want to move light and fast,

00:01:28.075 --> 00:01:31.765
but still be prepared for anything the mountain can throw at them.

00:01:34.680 --> 00:01:36.227
It's about having one pack you can

00:01:36.360 --> 00:01:39.180
trust for many different kinds of trips.

00:01:41.446 --> 00:01:45.961
It's great for anyone who enjoys exploring mountains safely and comfortably.

00:01:48.485 --> 00:01:52.258
In mountains, picking the right gear is key for safety.

00:01:53.579 --> 00:01:56.360
The 32-liter size helps you pack smart,

00:01:56.625 --> 00:01:59.487
carrying only essential, lightweight items

00:01:59.760 --> 00:02:01.924
without sacrificing safety.

00:02:03.377 --> 00:02:05.713
Packing lighter means you can move easier,

00:02:05.823 --> 00:02:09.051
feel less tired, and enjoy your time in the mountains more.

00:02:09.902 --> 00:02:12.668
This pack is perfect size to carrying everything you need

00:02:12.817 --> 00:02:14.160
and nothing you don't.

00:02:15.418 --> 00:02:16.856
A great thing about this pack

00:02:16.942 --> 00:02:20.004
is how easy it adjusts for different trip lengths.

00:02:20.129 --> 00:02:22.694
Whether you are heading out for a one-day hike

00:02:23.031 --> 00:02:24.333
or a five-day adventure,

00:02:24.608 --> 00:02:28.686
you can compress it down for light load or expand it to carry more.

00:02:29.927 --> 00:02:34.021
The rolltop closure lets you size it from 32-liters down to 14,

00:02:34.396 --> 00:02:36.865
keeping your gear packed tight and secure

00:02:37.005 --> 00:02:38.810
no matter how much you are carrying.

00:02:40.279 --> 00:02:42.193
So if you start a trip with a lot of food,

00:02:42.482 --> 00:02:46.201
the pack gets more and more stable as you eat it.

00:02:46.427 --> 00:02:49.240
It's always the right size for what you are carrying.

00:02:50.870 --> 00:02:53.042
To keep it super compact and secure,

00:02:53.236 --> 00:02:56.837
you can properly buckle the rolltop down to the side of the pack.

00:02:57.419 --> 00:02:59.763
But for those quick, convenient moments,

00:02:59.948 --> 00:03:01.987
there is also what I call "lazy way".

00:03:02.452 --> 00:03:05.818
You can simply connect the buckle to each other over the top,

00:03:06.110 --> 00:03:09.333
even when you are wearing the vest for quick closure.

00:03:09.867 --> 00:03:13.056
This is super handy when I am constantly pulling out jackets

00:03:13.203 --> 00:03:16.287
or snacks for my daughters during a family trip.

00:03:17.468 --> 00:03:19.326
The mountains in Taiwan can be very tough

00:03:19.858 --> 00:03:22.434
so being safe and comfortable is very important,

00:03:22.625 --> 00:03:24.387
especially on longer trips.

00:03:24.691 --> 00:03:28.232
The Tornado Vest Pack has enough room without limiting your movement

00:03:28.510 --> 00:03:31.166
keeping you comfortable, even on rough trails.

00:03:31.487 --> 00:03:34.446
After all, who likes to carry a heavy bouncy backpack?

00:03:35.080 --> 00:03:37.510
This vest fits close to your body,

00:03:37.675 --> 00:03:41.660
so it feels more likea piece of clothing than a big, heavy bag.

00:03:42.424 --> 00:03:48.173
The Tornado Vest Pack uses strong 100D ripstop fabric, light but very durable.

00:03:48.468 --> 00:03:51.810
The ripstop fabric stops smaller tears from growing bigger,

00:03:52.001 --> 00:03:54.137
adding durability without extra weight.

00:03:54.822 --> 00:03:59.569
It also has a polycarbonate coating, which is tougher than standard coatings.

00:04:00.471 --> 00:04:03.588
It's strong waterproof up to 2000mm

00:04:03.839 --> 00:04:06.869
and resists UV damage and wear from rubbing.

00:04:07.312 --> 00:04:11.811
I always recommend using waterproof liners or dry bags inside the pack.

00:04:12.661 --> 00:04:14.606
The weather can be really unforgiving.

00:04:15.292 --> 00:04:18.781
And under mechanical load, no fabric is perfectly waterproof.

00:04:19.389 --> 00:04:21.453
Your main goal should always be to keep

00:04:21.601 --> 00:04:24.361
your sleeping bag and warm clothing dry.

00:04:25.003 --> 00:04:26.384
It is frameless pack.

00:04:26.592 --> 00:04:30.024
There is no heavy frame, keeping the Vest Pack very light.

00:04:30.611 --> 00:04:32.272
But here is the clever part.

00:04:32.767 --> 00:04:34.920
We have included a special compartment

00:04:35.033 --> 00:04:38.366
on the backside of the pack for 4-segment Mpad,

00:04:38.991 --> 00:04:40.615
which comes included.

00:04:41.695 --> 00:04:45.098
You can easily insert it for more support and weight distribution,

00:04:45.358 --> 00:04:48.596
and you can also attach a simple hip belt for even better stability.

00:04:49.178 --> 00:04:51.461
This is great, because you can choose.

00:04:51.704 --> 00:04:54.516
If you won't go super light, you don't need the pad.

00:04:55.054 --> 00:04:56.534
If you have a heavier load,

00:04:56.727 --> 00:05:00.735
put the pad in for extra comfort and protection to your back.

00:05:01.352 --> 00:05:04.320
It's all about adapting the pack to your adventure.

00:05:05.196 --> 00:05:09.371
There are three big meshpockets on the outside for more space.

00:05:10.283 --> 00:05:14.243
The big pocket in front is great for drying wet things,

00:05:14.415 --> 00:05:16.784
like rain jacket or wet socks.

00:05:17.262 --> 00:05:21.333
The pockets on the sides are easy to reach without taking the pack off.

00:05:21.715 --> 00:05:23.737
There is also a pocket on the bottom,

00:05:23.972 --> 00:05:27.374
perfect for things you use a lot during a hike.

00:05:28.173 --> 00:05:29.857
The chest straps are elastic,

00:05:29.987 --> 00:05:32.713
so they are comfortable and keeping the pack stable.

00:05:33.514 --> 00:05:37.915
Here in the front, you have pockets for two soft flasks.

00:05:38.410 --> 00:05:42.299
There are also special pockets which can carry your phone or action camera.

00:05:42.994 --> 00:05:47.813
It has a waterproof layer inside, to shield your phone from your sweat.

00:05:48.316 --> 00:05:51.007
It's a small detail that makes a big difference,

00:05:51.164 --> 00:05:53.395
preventing that annoying lens moisture

00:05:53.560 --> 00:05:57.174
you often get when pulling your phone out for a quick photo.

00:05:57.920 --> 00:06:01.722
The Vest Pack come with our 700ml soft Beast flask.

00:06:02.104 --> 00:06:04.268
It's perfect for drinking on the trail

00:06:04.468 --> 00:06:06.803
and it fits exactly in the front pockets.

00:06:07.410 --> 00:06:11.230
It holds a good amount of water for when you are on the move.

00:06:12.089 --> 00:06:13.704
Safety is the most important thing.

00:06:14.259 --> 00:06:17.212
That's why there is a special pocket on the shoulder

00:06:17.394 --> 00:06:20.996
for an emergency satellite device like Garmin inReach.

00:06:21.647 --> 00:06:24.509
It's always in place where you can reach it fast

00:06:24.613 --> 00:06:27.365
in emergency every second counts.

00:06:28.528 --> 00:06:31.445
You can't waste time digging for your satellite messenger,

00:06:31.688 --> 00:06:36.135
plus it needs a clear view of the sky to get a signal.

00:06:37.125 --> 00:06:39.520
This pocket keeps it in perfect spot,

00:06:39.737 --> 00:06:42.324
easy to reach and ready to connect.

00:06:42.862 --> 00:06:45.736
Moving to the back, we have the rear zipper pocket

00:06:45.979 --> 00:06:49.366
featuring a YKK water-resistant zipper.

00:06:49.738 --> 00:06:51.881
This is my secure zone for items

00:06:51.976 --> 00:06:54.617
which I don't need to access frequently during the day,

00:06:54.799 --> 00:06:58.044
but I like keep them separately from the main chamber.

00:06:58.799 --> 00:07:02.295
I typically store my headlamp here after sunrise

00:07:02.451 --> 00:07:05.168
or spare action camera batteries during a hike.

00:07:06.392 --> 00:07:08.603
It is also fine for keeping some cash

00:07:08.710 --> 00:07:11.913
or small items protected during family trips.

00:07:13.007 --> 00:07:15.108
Inside there is a mesh pocket.

00:07:15.507 --> 00:07:17.684
You can use it to hold a waterblader

00:07:17.884 --> 00:07:19.950
or you can use it for small electronics

00:07:19.985 --> 00:07:21.721
like a laptop or a tablet.

00:07:22.285 --> 00:07:25.158
This makes pack useful not just for the trail

00:07:25.238 --> 00:07:27.330
but also for commuting or traveling.

00:07:28.250 --> 00:07:30.602
The pack comes in a few sizes.

00:07:30.854 --> 00:07:34.604
Small is often good for women and medium for men.

00:07:35.402 --> 00:07:39.230
Recently, Hanchor also made a large size for bigger guys.

00:07:40.462 --> 00:07:45.115
The total weight of the west pack with Mpad is about 650 grams.

00:07:45.662 --> 00:07:48.162
The pack itself is only 500 grams.

00:07:48.422 --> 00:07:52.134
That is very light for a pack that can do so much.

00:07:52.429 --> 00:07:54.304
Go solo or tough terrain

00:07:54.817 --> 00:07:57.994
then taking helmet is a good idea for your safety.

00:07:58.497 --> 00:08:03.497
You can also get the optional strap with a carabiner and hook in our e-shop

00:08:03.732 --> 00:08:06.299
and use it to attach your helmet to the pack.

00:08:06.898 --> 00:08:11.082
This is perfect if you are climbing or doing anything where you need a helmet.

00:08:11.961 --> 00:08:14.695
It keeps your helmet secure on the outside of the pack

00:08:14.886 --> 00:08:19.226
so it doesn't take up space inside and easy to grab when you need it.

00:08:20.442 --> 00:08:24.667
In conclusion, the Tornado Vest Pack by Hanchor and Beast Runners

00:08:24.913 --> 00:08:27.578
is versatile, safe and comfortable.

00:08:27.777 --> 00:08:29.852
If it looks good for your next adventure,

00:08:30.060 --> 00:08:32.968
click the link in the description to learn more.

00:08:34.514 --> 00:08:38.465
Whether it's a short or a long hike or just a family trip

00:08:38.621 --> 00:08:40.487
this Vest Pack keeps up with you.

00:08:41.147 --> 00:08:42.302
Be safe out there!

00:09:06.758 --> 00:09:08.758
www.beast.run

